# The gateway image builds from the REPO ROOT (so it can COPY platformlib — see
# gateway/Dockerfile). Send Docker only what that build needs; everything else (models, datasets,
# node_modules, specs, .git) stays out of the build context.
#
# Codex round 6 (018): with last-match-wins rules, `!gateway` alone re-includes only the
# directory ENTRY on some builders — descendants like gateway/requirements.txt can still match
# the leading `*` and the first COPY fails. The `/**` forms re-include the contents explicitly,
# which is correct on both the classic builder and BuildKit.
*
!gateway
!gateway/**
!platformlib
!platformlib/**
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
